FBIS4-35019 "drlat124_k_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Menem Reaffirms No Intervention in Haiti Menem Reaffirms No Intervention in Haiti PY2706173594 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 PY2706173594 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network Spanish BFN [Text] President Carlos Menem emphasized today that Argentina will not participate in a probable military intervention in Haiti outside UN resolutions. The Argentine president guaranteed that the government will ask Congress for authorization if the United Nations makes a decision for our country to send military forces to that Caribbean island where a coup overthrew a democratic president in 1991. President Carlos Menem also urged the United States to increase political and economic measures against Haiti's de facto government in order to restore the democratic system in that country.
